{
  "stem": "27340.5",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the Germans were still very, very conscious of the War, A, that they'd lost it, and B, of the atrocities that they had committed not only towards Jews, but to many other what they called 'minority' or 'minor' sort of societies-- Poles, Ukrainians, Russians, Gypsies, Estonians, and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was at first a little difficult, especially since I had to be very careful not to let them understand or let them to get to know that I was, in fact, born in Germany and that I was a refugee, and that would have been harmful to my basically business associations with them.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was there on a business term.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was hired into the company to train the system in some technological development, whatever it may have been.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And if they would have known I was born in Germany and Jewish, I would have had to suffer from a lot of emotional problems.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They would have had either a lot of sympathy with me, or otherwise they would have hated my guts.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Neither of those things would have been helpful in a purely business association.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But after a few years in Germany and reflecting upon it, I found a lot of very good people there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "By good, I'm mean human beings-- not good as engineers, but as human beings-- that they fundamentally have no other interests than we have.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the fact that many of them got involved in this sort of Nazi ideology and were literally forced to play a part in it was their misfortune.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, we certainly can criticize them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'd often discussed that them with them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Why did you make it so easy to join in their sort of throng?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They basically had no alternatives.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
